  "text": "Once in the nucleus, the viral genome replicates to a low level number of copies per cell. The genome copy number in the basal cells is low, as the viral genome cannot be detected by in situ techniques during this stage [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The infected cell maintains this low copy number as the viral DNA replicates during subsequent cell divisions in the maintenance replication phase (Figure 3) .",
